[~vasya],

Yes, EC2_URL is set when you source eucarc.  If you don't source eucarc, then try to use any esi-* tool, you get the following:
{code}
[root@a-18 ~]# esi-describe-images
Error: Unable to find EC2_URL
Make sure your eucarc is sourced.
{code}
This is due to the following check in {{/usr/lib/python2.6/site-packages/esitoolsupport/__init__.py}}:
{code}
def check_environment():
    if not "EC2_URL" in os.environ.copy():
        print >> sys.stderr, "Error: Unable to find EC2_URL"
        print >> sys.stderr, "Make sure your eucarc is sourced."
        sys.exit(1)
    for b in [['/usr/bin/euare-accountlist'], ['/usr/bin/euctl', '-U', _get_properties_url()]]:
        _check_binary(b)
{code}

Fixed.

Eucalyptus Admin Tools Version: {{4.2.0-0.0.23957.682.20151001git294b61a.el6}}
